---
title: Vegan Cali-Style Zucchini & ’Shroom Bowls with Lemon Herb Rice & Creamy Avocado Sauce
description: Get ready for a California-style vegan rice bowl overflowing with a bounty of veggies! You’ll top a fluffy bed of lemon-herb jasmine rice with tender, garlicky roasted zucchini, tomato, and red onion. Next come the mushrooms, sautéed with oregano until crisp and golden brown. Drizzle this beautiful bowl with a bright lemon-parsley guacamole sauce for an inspired dinner that shines a spotlight on just how delicious fresh vegetables can be (when you show ‘em a little love).
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/64bfcd948e7c223eb5b36401-56e0bad2.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/64bfcd948e7c223eb5b36401.pdf
time required: 35 minutes
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 630 kcal
  fat: 25 g
  saturated fat: 3.5 g
  carbohydrates: 96 g
  sugar: 19 g
  protein: 11 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 390 mg
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/vegan-cali-style-zucchini-and-shroom-bowls-64bfcd948e7c223eb5b36401
servings: 2
---

Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 450 degrees.

In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, 1¼ cups water, and a
large pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to a
low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, wash and dry produce.

Slice @zucchini{1} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces. (TIP: If your
zucchini is large, halve lengthwise first.) Cut @tomato{1} into
½-inch-thick wedges. Halve, peel, and cut @red onion{1} into
½-inch-thick wedges.

In a #large bowl{}, toss zucchini, tomato, and onion with
@roasted onion & garlic spread{1%ounce}, a large drizzle of
@cooking oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{} until veggies are coated.

Transfer to a foil-lined #baking sheet{} in an even layer. Roast on middle
rack until browned and tender, ~{14-16%minutes}.

Meanwhile, trim and quarter @button mushrooms{8%ounce}. (skip if your
mushrooms are pre-sliced!) Zest and quarter @lemon{1}. Roughly chop
@parsley{1/4%ounce}.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a #large pan{} over
medium-high heat. Add mushrooms and @dried oregano{1%tsp}. Cook, stirring
occasionally, until browned and slightly crispy, ~{5-7%minutes}. Season with
salt and pepper. Transfer to a paper-towel-lined #plate{}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @vegan mayo{2%tbsp}, @guacamole{4%tbsp}, half
the parsley, and juice from one lemon wedge.

Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.
Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in remaining parsley, a big pinch of lemon
zest, and juice from one lemon wedge. Taste and season with salt and
pepper.

Divide rice between shallow #bowls{}. Top with roasted veggies and
mushrooms; drizzle with avocado sauce. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on
the side.